---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import BookLayout from '../../layouts/BookLayout.astro';
import { buildToc } from '../../lib/toc';
import ClinicalAccuracyDashboard from '../../components/ClinicalAccuracyDashboard.astro';

const toc = buildToc(await getCollection('book'));
---

<BookLayout title="Clinical accuracy-chain dashboard" toc={toc}>
  <h1>Clinical accuracy-chain dashboard</h1>
  <p class="lead">
    <strong>Clinical accuracy ≠ sensor accuracy</strong> (Ch. 29 §29.7). What reaches
    the patient is the root-sum-square of five independent terms: the tracker, the
    patient-to-image registration, the tip/instrument offset, target motion
    (respiration, cardiac), and residual distortion.
  </p>
  <p>
    Drag the sliders and watch the variance shares. With a 1 mm tracker behind a 2 mm
    registration and a 0.9 mm tip lever, the clinical number sits near 2.4 mm — and
    the <em>Halve the tracker</em> button shows that engineering the sensor to 0.5 mm
    barely moves it. The dominant term is registration or motion, not the tracker;
    that is where the clinical accuracy is won or lost.
  </p>
  <ClinicalAccuracyDashboard />
</BookLayout>
